WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:57.917 --> 00:59.375
--Argh!

01:02.084 --> 01:03.334
--Argh! Argh!

01:03.501 --> 01:05.584
--Ooh!

01:23.959 --> 01:26.084
Far, far away

01:26.251 --> 01:28.668
<i>in a magical part of the world,</i>

01:28.834 --> 01:31.251
<i>there is</i> a <i>special place</i> -

01:31.417 --> 01:34.084
<i>the sleepy town
of Warrnambool.</i>

01:35.751 --> 01:39.626
<i>Where fairy penguins</i> -
<i>the littlest penguins of all</i> -

01:39.792 --> 01:41.625
<i>call home.</i>

01:45.709 --> 01:49.001
<i>They nest on a rocky place
called Middle Island.</i>

01:50.001 --> 01:52.209
<i>For years,
the townspeople</i>

01:52.376 --> 01:54.751
<i>walked the shallow channel
to the island</i>

01:54.917 --> 01:59.417
<i>to watch thousands of fairy
penguins return home at night.</i>

02:01.751 --> 02:06.209
<i>Because the penguins brought
a special magic to the town.</i>

02:10.417 --> 02:12.334
<i>But one night,</i>

02:12.501 --> 02:15.793
<i>foxes found that they too
could walk to the island.</i>

02:20.501 --> 02:23.168
<i>And in just
a few short years...</i>

02:26.709 --> 02:29.459
<i>...there were hardly
any penguins left.</i>

02:33.876 --> 02:35.793
<i>And there was nothing
the townspeople</i>

02:35.959 --> 02:37.917
<i>could do to save them.</i>

02:55.542 --> 02:57.500
This is just awful.

02:57.667 --> 03:00.042
Especially if you're a penguin.

03:00.209 --> 03:03.501
Jack, Zoe,
how many penguins are left?

03:03.667 --> 03:06.000
You know, I'm gonna let Watt
be the angel of doom.

03:07.042 --> 03:10.750
Em, look, you should know that
the numbers aren't great, OK?

03:12.084 --> 03:14.042
Morning, Emily.
Sorry to be the...

03:14.209 --> 03:16.209
- How many, Mr Watt?
-20.

03:16.376 --> 03:18.293
W-what?
You just did your count.

03:18.459 --> 03:20.376
Maybe some left already.

03:20.542 --> 03:23.917
Zoe did her count at dawn before
they go out to hunt. It's 20.

03:24.084 --> 03:27.251
I remember when there were
thousands here. What a shame.

03:27.417 --> 03:29.334
Maybe they're just staying out
to protect themselves.

03:29.501 --> 03:31.459
We just need to hold
the foxes off a little while.

03:31.626 --> 03:33.584
- How? With tranquilliser guns?
-Yeah.

03:33.751 --> 03:35.959
- See how well that's been going.
-I was actually doing alright

03:36.126 --> 03:38.251
till the foxes defied nature
and learnt how to swim.

03:38.417 --> 03:41.334
Listen, your annual review
is in two weeks.

03:41.501 --> 03:43.751
To keep funding
and sanctuary status,

03:43.917 --> 03:46.542
you need at least 10 penguins
to call this place home.

03:46.709 --> 03:50.542
- And at this rate...
-Mr Watt, Paul, please.

03:50.709 --> 03:53.917
You knew my mum. This sanctuary
was her everything.

03:54.084 --> 03:56.459
I can't let her down. Please.

03:56.626 --> 03:59.167
That's why I've stuck my neck
out with council for so long.

03:59.334 --> 04:01.292
I'm sorry, Emily.

04:01.459 --> 04:04.209
But if council sees less
than 10 penguins next month,

04:04.376 --> 04:07.834
the place won't be a sanctuary,
it'll just be a rock.

04:09.334 --> 04:11.709
So now what do we do?

04:11.876 --> 04:14.709
Well, unless things take a turn,
we're all out of work.

04:17.166 --> 04:20.209
<i>With the fairy
penguins almost gone,</i>

04:20.375 --> 04:22.417
<i>it seems
the magic of Warrnambool</i>

04:22.584 --> 04:24.792
<i>will soon be gone too.</i>

04:26.667 --> 04:29.751
<i>The town's only hope
now lies with...</i>

04:31.376 --> 04:34.834
<i>...a chicken farmer
and his very odd dog.</i>

04:35.001 --> 04:37.667
<i>-- They just don't know it yet.</i>

04:37.834 --> 04:39.834
Right. Ugh!

04:40.001 --> 04:42.209
Brrr! Brrr!

04:44.001 --> 04:46.084
Brrr!

04:48.334 --> 04:50.251
Ah, yes!

04:50.417 --> 04:54.042
Nothing like a good
cold kick to the ventricles

04:54.209 --> 04:56.251
to start the day, eh, ladies?

05:01.042 --> 05:02.667
Oh.

05:07.001 --> 05:08.584
Mmm!

05:09.626 --> 05:11.292
Beautiful!

05:17.876 --> 05:19.876
Morning, Missy.

05:23.334 --> 05:25.584
Oddball! Breakfast!

05:28.542 --> 05:30.459
Oddball, where are you, mate?

05:44.042 --> 05:46.417
Oh! Get out of there!

05:46.584 --> 05:49.959
How many times do I have
to tell you, you crazy dog?

05:50.126 --> 05:53.042
Here. That's your food.

05:53.209 --> 05:55.751
What are you waiting for -
a knife and fork? Just eat it up.

05:59.001 --> 06:01.251
Right, your turn to shower.

06:03.626 --> 06:06.042
The only Maremma dog
in history

06:06.209 --> 06:08.292
that can't bring itself
to guard chickens.

06:08.459 --> 06:10.084
Explain that to me.

06:10.251 --> 06:12.751
Huh?
Give me one good reason

06:12.917 --> 06:15.376
why I shouldn't trade you in
to the highest bidder.

06:15.542 --> 06:18.334
- Not that I'd get much for you.

06:20.792 --> 06:23.917
There's a good one, then.

06:35.709 --> 06:38.709
You! You're still grounded.

06:38.876 --> 06:41.792
So stay. OK?

06:41.959 --> 06:44.209
I'm off to pick up Livvie.

06:44.376 --> 06:46.459
And don't destroy anything!

06:48.001 --> 06:50.042
And if you do,
glue it back together

06:50.209 --> 06:52.126
so I don't know about it.

06:53.251 --> 06:55.167
Another day, another dozen.

06:56.667 --> 06:59.917
What happened to 'stay'? Eh?

07:00.084 --> 07:03.042
You are dopey if you think
you're coming into town with me.

07:03.209 --> 07:06.209
--Alright.

07:06.376 --> 07:09.167
Well, move over. Go on.
Shove over.

07:09.334 --> 07:11.042
Go on, over you get.

07:12.084 --> 07:15.167
Keep your head down
and your mouth shut.

07:15.334 --> 07:17.709
Took me six months
to pay off your last debt.

07:17.876 --> 07:22.209
Move over!
Alright. Off we go.

08:01.209 --> 08:04.626
I am really sorry
about the penguins, Olivia.

08:04.792 --> 08:07.876
You know, I'm sure that
your mom and her team,

08:08.042 --> 08:09.959
they're doing
everything they can.

08:10.126 --> 08:13.251
They're very smart.
Um...

08:13.417 --> 08:16.709
But, hey, you know what?
This gives us a chance to bond.

08:17.917 --> 08:21.209
Right? No? Maybe not.

08:24.209 --> 08:26.126
Hey, Olivia,
we're in a bit of a hurry.

08:26.292 --> 08:28.542
Did you get your bag
all packed?

08:28.709 --> 08:31.251
- Bag's on the table.
-Ah!

08:31.417 --> 08:33.333
Good. Of course you did,
of course you did.

08:33.501 --> 08:36.792
Because you...are mature.
You're an adult.

08:36.958 --> 08:40.333
What are you? You're, like...
you're, like, 30 or 35, 36.

08:40.501 --> 08:42.542
I'm 9.

08:42.708 --> 08:45.376
I know, I was joking. A joke.

08:45.542 --> 08:48.001
Hey, I was going to wait
until your mom got here,

08:48.167 --> 08:50.834
but no time like the present.

08:51.001 --> 08:53.667
--OK, well, that is for you.

08:53.834 --> 08:55.751
Just to say thank you
for being such a good hostess.

08:55.917 --> 08:57.834
Did you want crust or no crust?

08:58.001 --> 09:00.501
I always do no crust.
I'm going to do no crust.

09:01.709 --> 09:03.126
Thanks.

09:03.292 --> 09:05.209
I heard that everyone
is wearing those now.

09:05.376 --> 09:07.917
And why would I want to
be like everyone else?

09:08.084 --> 09:10.626
Oh...that's right.

09:10.792 --> 09:13.667
Your mom told me that you were
a bit of a trailblazer. No!

09:16.626 --> 09:18.876
Hey. Emily!

09:19.042 --> 09:21.292
No. No, no.
Everything's great.

09:21.459 --> 09:23.542
Right? Huh?

09:23.709 --> 09:27.334
No, we're having
a wonderful time.

09:27.501 --> 09:30.292
Don't worry about it. Huh?

09:30.459 --> 09:33.334
What? Your dad?

09:33.501 --> 09:36.251
When? No, no, no, no.
You said he was never on time.

09:36.417 --> 09:38.209
<i>Livvie. Calling Livvie.</i>

09:38.376 --> 09:40.292
<i>Out the from'
in T minus 10 seconds.</i>

09:40.459 --> 09:42.584
Copy, Grandad.
Be right out. Over.

09:44.626 --> 09:47.959
- Got to go!
-He's here. What do I do?

09:50.084 --> 09:52.459
- Ah, there's my Livvie.
-Grandad, flip me over!

09:52.626 --> 09:55.126
Hang on, watch me back.
I can't flip you over anymore.

09:55.292 --> 09:57.584
You're too big.
You'll just pull me over.

09:57.751 --> 10:00.167
That's because you're
such a great big giant.

10:00.334 --> 10:04.292
Grandad, you're not supposed
to bring Oddball into town!

10:04.459 --> 10:06.917
--Oh, shoo!

10:07.084 --> 10:10.167
Shoo! Get away! Go!

10:10.334 --> 10:13.251
I see you in there.
Get out here now!

10:13.417 --> 10:15.834
If you don't, I'm gonna
come in there and drag you out.

10:16.001 --> 10:18.709
- Oh, no.

10:18.876 --> 10:20.876
Come on,
you dopey thing. Get out here!

10:21.042 --> 10:23.042
Not the tie!

10:23.209 --> 10:25.126
What have you
got there? Hey?

10:25.292 --> 10:27.167
Come on, show me
what you've got.

10:27.334 --> 10:28.959
Oh, yeah, he's got
a bit of fight, don't you?

10:29.126 --> 10:31.001
What is it?
Where did you get that?

10:31.167 --> 10:33.084
- Hi.
-Hey. Where have you been?

10:33.251 --> 10:35.751
- Uh...
- Hi, Mum!

10:38.251 --> 10:41.001
Hi. I'm so sorry.

10:41.167 --> 10:43.501
Our first morning together
has just turned into a mess.

10:43.667 --> 10:46.834
Oh, that's OK.
Hey, I like your mess.

10:47.001 --> 10:50.709
- Let's go.
-Go... Wait, go? Now?

10:50.876 --> 10:53.959
Yeah. He'll just come in
and then you'll be trapped.

10:54.126 --> 10:56.667
Don't worry. Keep it fast
and don't stop moving.

10:57.709 --> 10:59.626
- Hmm.
-Hi, Dad! Right.

10:59.792 --> 11:03.001
- Let's get going, eh?

11:03.167 --> 11:05.376
Hi. Uh, Bradley Slater.

11:05.542 --> 11:08.042
We've met, um...

11:09.501 --> 11:12.376
- Oh.

11:12.542 --> 11:14.459
Dad, Oddy's not
supposed to be in town.

11:14.626 --> 11:16.292
You can't afford
a repeat of last time.

11:16.459 --> 11:19.251
Well, this isn't town
and your yard's got a fence.

11:19.417 --> 11:22.792
Alright, we've all got
places to go and things to do.

11:22.959 --> 11:26.042
I've got a big rehearsal tonight
for the opening night.

11:26.209 --> 11:29.667
- Goodbye.
-What's he doing here?

11:29.834 --> 11:31.917
I was called away
early this morning

11:32.084 --> 11:34.501
and Bradley really helped
us out. You behaved, right?

11:34.667 --> 11:36.667
Oh, we're practically BFFs.

11:36.834 --> 11:39.542
Alright, come on, then.
Chop-chop. Hop into the truck.

11:39.709 --> 11:42.751
Bradley helped out, eh?

11:46.834 --> 11:50.542
Really? You and the
tourism blow-in, huh?

11:51.959 --> 11:54.792
<i>l...l</i> like him.

11:54.959 --> 11:57.126
And he's not scared away
by the single mum thing,

11:57.292 --> 11:59.417
so don't screw this up, OK?

12:00.917 --> 12:03.834
Alright.
It's none of my business.

12:04.876 --> 12:07.126
--Oh, just grind away, Betty.

12:07.292 --> 12:09.667
Come on, darling.
Hold your tongue to your left.

12:09.834 --> 12:11.501
--Too far.

12:11.667 --> 12:13.126
- Try the right.

12:13.292 --> 12:14.834
- No. Try the left.

12:15.001 --> 12:16.459
- No. Try the middle.

12:16.626 --> 12:18.667
Nope. Out more. Ah!

12:20.709 --> 12:22.501
Tongue out the middle.
Come on, Oddy!

12:22.667 --> 12:26.709
Uh, this Bradley,
what do you think?

12:26.876 --> 12:28.667
He tried to buy me off
with shoes.

12:28.834 --> 12:30.667
Lord help us.

12:30.834 --> 12:33.167
Well, you know if you ever need
anything, I'm always here.

12:33.334 --> 12:35.084
--Oddball!

12:35.251 --> 12:37.501
- Gross!
-Oh! Oh, wow.

12:37.667 --> 12:40.001
- Eugh, yuck!
-That'd make an onion cry.

12:40.167 --> 12:42.667
That is disgusting.
Definitely yuck!

12:42.834 --> 12:44.792
Oddball, that is wrong.

12:48.959 --> 12:50.626
Hello, little one.

12:58.834 --> 13:00.209
Reopening
the village

13:00.376 --> 13:02.042
is the first stop
in my tourism initiative.

13:02.209 --> 13:03.876
We have costumed re-enactors,

13:04.042 --> 13:05.792
this delightful
southern right whale.

13:05.959 --> 13:07.959
Oh, guys! I love you for
being on time. OK, here.

13:08.126 --> 13:10.042
Right, there. Nice
and slow. Come on, come on.

13:10.209 --> 13:11.876
Place it here.

13:12.042 --> 13:14.084
This is the piece de resistance
of the entire show.

13:14.251 --> 13:15.959
Is it good?

13:16.126 --> 13:18.209
There are only two of these
projectors in the entire world.

13:18.376 --> 13:20.751
You wouldn't believe the strings
I had to pull to get this.

13:20.917 --> 13:22.876
Alright, we will fire it up

13:23.042 --> 13:26.959
and then we project the movie
off the rising mist...

13:30.459 --> 13:33.251
The crowd will ooh and ah,
and in that moment, Ms Mayor,

13:33.417 --> 13:36.167
we will officially be
open for business.

13:38.917 --> 13:42.251
Good morning!
Have fun today. Hi!

13:48.626 --> 13:50.667
Ah, there you go.
And on time, to boot.

13:50.834 --> 13:52.542
--Oddy.

13:52.709 --> 13:54.917
See you this afternoon
when I pick you up.

13:56.251 --> 13:57.959
What's wrong?

13:58.126 --> 13:59.501
There was another penguin

13:59.667 --> 14:01.209
killed at the reserve
last night.

14:01.376 --> 14:03.501
That's why Mum wasn't home
this morning.

14:03.667 --> 14:06.292
Oh, right.
She's running out of options.

14:06.459 --> 14:08.751
They've tried everything.

14:08.917 --> 14:12.334
Well, I'm sure your mum
will come up with something.

14:12.501 --> 14:14.626
- She always seems <i>to...</i>
- Hey, Livvie. Hey, Oddball.

14:14.792 --> 14:18.001
Your friend's there.
See you after school, darl.

14:18.167 --> 14:20.167
- See ya.

14:20.334 --> 14:21.959
- Oddy!
- Oddball!

14:22.126 --> 14:23.792
He's taking another runner!
Go, Oddball!

14:23.959 --> 14:25.709
Livvie, shut the door,
shut the door!

14:25.876 --> 14:28.917
- Grandad, go!
- Seatbelt!

14:29.084 --> 14:31.001
Keen your eye on him.
Hang on.

14:31.167 --> 14:33.334
-Oddball!

14:33.501 --> 14:36.876
- Can you see him?
- There he is!

14:43.709 --> 14:46.709
Oh! Oh!

14:51.084 --> 14:53.251
Oh, my goodness!

15:17.751 --> 15:19.584
Oh, no.
He's turning around.

15:20.626 --> 15:23.167
- Oddball!
- You've gotta stop him!

15:24.417 --> 15:26.709
Ow!

15:27.751 --> 15:30.876
- Ooh!

15:34.501 --> 15:36.417
Stop that dog!

15:56.917 --> 15:59.584
Ooh! Ooh!

16:08.584 --> 16:10.042
Ow!

16:11.126 --> 16:13.042
By tomorrow morning,
everyone in Victoria

16:13.209 --> 16:16.667
will be saying the name
Warrnambool.

16:27.542 --> 16:28.917
Oddball!

16:29.084 --> 16:30.792
- Watch out!

16:30.959 --> 16:33.459
No,no,no,no,no,no!

16:42.251 --> 16:46.334
Ah! (GRUNTS) Ah!

16:46.501 --> 16:49.001
Somebody
secure the whale!

16:49.167 --> 16:51.626
Grab it, grab it,
grab it!

16:51.792 --> 16:53.709
That dog's
out of control.

16:55.459 --> 16:57.501
Sergeant Gosch to base.
We have a situation here.

17:04.291 --> 17:06.166
Judge Burns,
couldn't Oddball

17:06.334 --> 17:08.291
go to an obedience school?

17:08.459 --> 17:12.834
Miss Marsh, this is the third
time the dog's been in trouble.

17:13.001 --> 17:14.916
We have the support

17:15.084 --> 17:17.084
to fast-track
what needs to be done.

17:17.251 --> 17:19.459
And he is obviously dangerous.

17:19.626 --> 17:22.416
Huh! Oddball isn't dangerous.

17:22.584 --> 17:26.501
He's just...curious,
that's all.

17:27.541 --> 17:31.084
I'm sorry.
Your Honour, if I may?

17:31.251 --> 17:36.042
The tourism initiative is dead
unless this dog is alive.

17:36.209 --> 17:39.376
But that dog
ruined your hard work.

17:39.542 --> 17:42.001
Precisely. I know that.

17:42.167 --> 17:45.417
But that's why I don't want him
to ruin it again.

17:45.584 --> 17:47.959
Look, we can postpone
the reopening.

17:48.126 --> 17:50.917
That's not a problem.
But there's press in town.

17:51.959 --> 17:54.917
And there isn't a whaling
village in the entire world

17:55.084 --> 17:58.167
that can hold the news cycle

17:58.334 --> 18:01.084
like the story of
a broken-hearted little angel.

18:01.251 --> 18:03.292
A girl who loves her dog...

18:03.459 --> 18:06.376
--..she grew up loving.

18:06.542 --> 18:10.376
And, Your Honour, since it is
ultimately your decision,

18:10.542 --> 18:15.209
well, I guess
every story needs its villain.

18:16.251 --> 18:19.459
Mr Slater does make
a valid point.

18:19.626 --> 18:22.542
Yes, he does.

18:30.417 --> 18:32.917
Last chance, Mr Marsh.

18:33.084 --> 18:36.459
Oddball stays confined
to your farm.

18:36.626 --> 18:42.167
If he so much as sets one paw
within these city limits,

18:42.334 --> 18:44.251
it's the end of the line.

18:44.417 --> 18:46.167
Is that clear?

18:46.334 --> 18:50.501
- The end of the line!
-Yes.

18:51.876 --> 18:55.667
Case closed.

18:58.084 --> 19:01.334
Well, I gotta say that
Bradley bozo's got some chops.

19:01.501 --> 19:03.459
How can you be so cavalier
about this?

19:03.626 --> 19:05.584
We dodged a bullet in there.

19:05.751 --> 19:07.751
Oh, I'm just trying
to stay positive.

19:07.917 --> 19:10.167
What are you so bent about?

19:10.334 --> 19:12.709
Let's be honest. We've dodged
bigger bullets than this.

19:12.876 --> 19:15.251
Dad, I told you this already.
Look, none of this would

19:15.417 --> 19:17.376
have happened if you'd
listened to me this morning.

19:17.542 --> 19:19.459
- Let's go to the car. Come on.
-See ya, darl.

19:19.626 --> 19:21.751
- See ya.
-Dad...

19:21.917 --> 19:24.167
The penguins are almost gone.

19:24.334 --> 19:27.501
If we're below 10 next month,
council are shutting us down.

19:27.667 --> 19:30.417
Those bureaucrats!
They wouldn't know if they...

19:30.584 --> 19:32.709
It's not them
anymore, Dad.

19:32.876 --> 19:35.084
Nature is taking its course.

19:35.251 --> 19:36.959
No penguins
means no sanctuary.

19:37.126 --> 19:39.584
No sanctuary means no job
and...

19:40.626 --> 19:42.626
Well, there might not be
anything here for me.

19:42.792 --> 19:44.709
I have Livvie to think of.

19:44.876 --> 19:46.959
I will fight for the penguins,

19:47.126 --> 19:49.042
but I'm also thinking about
what's next.

19:49.209 --> 19:50.792
I'll tell you
what's next.

19:50.959 --> 19:52.876
I'm gonna march in there
and tell those imbeciles

19:53.042 --> 19:55.542
-they've gotta pull their...
-No, Dad! Dad! Just stop!

19:56.584 --> 19:59.501
Unless you can bring
the penguins back, just stop.

19:59.667 --> 20:01.751
You have done
more than enough for today.

20:22.751 --> 20:24.709
- Mum!

20:24.876 --> 20:26.792
Stop him now!

20:26.959 --> 20:28.876
- You're not a penguin, Dad.
- Come on, darling.

20:29.042 --> 20:30.834
Look at the camera
so I can see you.

20:31.001 --> 20:32.917
Give us a smile or something.

