39:09.042 --> 39:11.501
You look like a Maremma.

39:11.667 --> 39:13.626
Heck, you even
sound like a Maremma.

39:13.792 --> 39:15.709
But I want you to show me
that somewhere

39:15.876 --> 39:17.917
inside that crazy dog routine
you've got going on

39:18.084 --> 39:20.042
that you actually
are a Maremma.

39:20.209 --> 39:22.251
Let's go save
some penguins, eh?

39:22.417 --> 39:24.376
Right.

39:24.542 --> 39:26.501
Actually, Livvie,
you should do this.

39:26.667 --> 39:29.709
I don't think they can jail
a minor.

39:29.876 --> 39:33.084
- Risk it for the biscuit.
-That's right.

39:39.959 --> 39:42.459
- Are you alright?
-Yeah.

39:43.542 --> 39:46.542
That's it, Oddy.
Get used to that penguin scent.

39:49.042 --> 39:52.001
Don't worry, mate.
Your friends will be here soon.

39:56.167 --> 39:58.251
Hey, here they come.

39:59.542 --> 40:02.667
- Oh, wow.
- Ooh!

40:10.834 --> 40:13.334
Go on, Pocket.
Go see your friends.

40:22.709 --> 40:26.542
Now, let's see
what Oddy's made of.

40:31.251 --> 40:33.209
- Ah!

40:40.001 --> 40:42.084
Oh.

40:43.126 --> 40:46.417
What do you know?
This might actually work.

41:08.167 --> 41:10.126
What's happening?

41:24.292 --> 41:25.876
Ha.

41:35.292 --> 41:37.209
Grandma's proud of us.

41:37.376 --> 41:39.167
How do you
figure that?

41:39.334 --> 41:43.084
Well...when it's Windy,

41:43.251 --> 41:45.417
she's blowing us kisses.

41:46.959 --> 41:52.167
And when the sun sparkles
off the water, she's laughing.

41:52.334 --> 41:56.459
And up there,
she's on every star in the sky

41:56.626 --> 41:58.959
looking out for us.

42:03.917 --> 42:05.876
Who's told you that?

42:06.917 --> 42:10.209
Mum did.
She tells me all the time.

42:17.334 --> 42:19.417
You can see half
the world from up here.

42:21.626 --> 42:24.292
I sound so small town.
I'm sorry.

42:24.459 --> 42:26.542
Not at all.

42:28.834 --> 42:32.626
If you want to see
the other half of the world,

42:32.792 --> 42:35.042
maybe we could start
with New York.

42:36.626 --> 42:38.667
Yeah, maybe.

42:38.834 --> 42:41.376
- Maybe?
-Maybe.

42:41.542 --> 42:44.667
- Yeah, maybe.
<i>-l'll</i> take that as a yes.

42:55.126 --> 42:57.084
Oddy, mate, get off me!

42:57.251 --> 42:59.751
- Give it a break, huh?
-Get up, sleepyhead.

42:59.917 --> 43:02.126
We've got to get off the island
before Zoe gets here.

43:02.292 --> 43:04.751
Alright, alright,
just give us a minute, will you?

43:04.917 --> 43:08.501
-

43:08.667 --> 43:12.376
You realise if Oddy
nails his solo run tonight,

43:12.542 --> 43:15.584
we are tickety-boo.

43:15.751 --> 43:18.292
Not a word to your mum,
alright? Hmm?

43:18.459 --> 43:20.001
Pinky?

43:24.626 --> 43:27.251
- Hi!
-Hi, Mum!

43:27.417 --> 43:29.501
Oh, I missed you.

43:31.084 --> 43:33.334
You and Grandad didn't
get into any trouble, did you?

43:33.501 --> 43:35.626
Trouble? Us? Of course not!

43:35.792 --> 43:37.876
--How was your trip?

43:38.042 --> 43:40.417
Oh, you know, I think
I might've caught the travel bug.

43:40.584 --> 43:42.792
--Oh, this is for you.

43:42.959 --> 43:45.751
This is for your adventures.
You can take pictures with it.

43:45.917 --> 43:49.626
- You can make movies.
-Cool! Thanks.

43:50.709 --> 43:53.417
I even missed you,
you hairball.

43:53.584 --> 43:56.126
Hey?

43:56.292 --> 43:58.209
Thanks for looking
after Liv, Dad.

43:58.376 --> 44:00.626
I hope it wasn't too much.

44:00.792 --> 44:02.792
My friend has one.

44:02.959 --> 44:05.001
You can put all your meetings
in there.

44:05.167 --> 44:09.001
Mm-hm. Her one's pink.
Yeah, it's so cool.

44:13.501 --> 44:15.626
Never as much as you want.

44:46.084 --> 44:48.376
And good evening,
Pocket.

44:49.501 --> 44:51.417
Off you go, mate.

44:55.251 --> 44:57.251
Hang on.
What have we got here?

44:57.417 --> 45:01.792
--Hey, she's got her eye on you!

45:01.959 --> 45:04.542
You're right. You're looking
good. Your Wing's all better.

45:05.626 --> 45:08.584
Hey, mate, she's coming over.

45:08.751 --> 45:12.876
- Go on. Go and say hello.

45:13.042 --> 45:15.376
You've got your tuxedo on.
Ask her to dance.

45:20.959 --> 45:23.459
Whoops!
OK, so you're not a dancer.

45:23.626 --> 45:26.876
- Can you sing?

45:27.042 --> 45:28.959
There you go.

45:32.334 --> 45:36.084
Hey, look confident.
Not too confident.

45:38.626 --> 45:41.876
Hang on, what are you doing?
You need to invite her in.

45:44.334 --> 45:45.834
That's better.

45:48.667 --> 45:52.751
Bingo. Ha! Job done.

45:53.792 --> 45:55.709
Alright, mate.

45:55.876 --> 45:57.792
I'll leave you with it,
alright?

45:57.959 --> 46:00.084
See you tomorrow. Ugh!

46:05.459 --> 46:10.084
--Ah, stay. Stay! Sit down.

46:10.251 --> 46:14.167
I'll be back.
You'll be right.

46:14.334 --> 46:18.001
--Uh-uh. Stay. Just wait there.

46:18.167 --> 46:20.876
This is your job now.

46:21.042 --> 46:24.042
Stay there. That's right.
Good.

46:24.209 --> 46:26.167
Hang on. Oh, oh, oh!

46:26.334 --> 46:28.584
- Ow!

46:28.751 --> 46:31.251
I'm alright.
Stay where you are.

46:48.959 --> 46:51.876
Alright, Betty, let's go home.

48:08.834 --> 48:12.584
- Oddy, where are you, mate?

48:19.542 --> 48:21.626
This isn't going to work,
is it?

48:30.917 --> 48:33.001
Did you have a dust-up
with a fox, mate?

48:43.917 --> 48:46.292
Well, spin me frisbee.

48:47.417 --> 48:49.876
om

48:52.292 --> 48:54.584
Looks like we're in business.

49:01.876 --> 49:03.959
See you tomorrow, Jack.

49:04.126 --> 49:06.209
Have a good one, Swampy.

49:11.834 --> 49:14.626
Alright, I'm ready.
Where are we?

49:15.792 --> 49:18.251
Hey, Em,
when you met Bradley,

49:18.417 --> 49:21.001
like...how did you know
that he was the one?

49:21.167 --> 49:23.876
15? We haven't lost any?

49:24.042 --> 49:26.292
Nup. I wouldn't go
getting too excited.

49:26.459 --> 49:28.417
There's probably
a couple of nomads in there.

49:28.584 --> 49:30.501
WOW! Ha!

49:30.667 --> 49:32.792
They're not laying eggs, so...

49:35.126 --> 49:37.626
Great. Good chat.

49:42.917 --> 49:44.917
We're still holding at 15! Oh!

49:47.459 --> 49:49.626
Alright. Seatbelt.

49:49.792 --> 49:51.876
Oh, a dashboard dance first.

49:52.917 --> 49:54.251
Yes!

49:57.542 --> 49:59.084
'Bye!

50:07.667 --> 50:09.751
You know,
we should do this more often.

50:11.542 --> 50:14.376
I know Bradley has been
hanging around a lot lately.

50:14.542 --> 50:16.626
You two been
getting on alright?

50:17.667 --> 50:19.667
He's not awful.

50:21.251 --> 50:24.334
-

50:25.417 --> 50:28.251
So, no fox attacks
in the past few nights, huh?

50:28.417 --> 50:33.042
Yeah. But try not to get
your hopes up, OK?

50:33.209 --> 50:35.126
'Cause it might
just be a fluke.

50:35.292 --> 50:38.626
Oh, it's no fluke.
Everything's gonna be fine.

50:38.792 --> 50:41.542
Maybe,
but we should talk about

50:41.709 --> 50:44.084
what will happen
if the sanctuary does close.

50:44.251 --> 50:46.167
You know,
keep our options open.

50:46.334 --> 50:49.584
But you can't just give up.
Breeding season's soon, right?

50:49.751 --> 50:51.667
Well, I'm not giving up.

50:51.834 --> 50:54.167
I'm just...l'm not
ruling anything out.

50:56.709 --> 50:58.376
Sweetheart...

50:59.751 --> 51:02.292
If Bradley's projects
in town go well,

51:02.459 --> 51:06.167
then...he might have some
opportunities with his company.

51:06.334 --> 51:09.626
And those might be
opportunities for us too.

51:09.792 --> 51:13.792
Wait, you mean
like...moving away?

51:15.251 --> 51:17.209
It's a possibility.

51:17.376 --> 51:19.292
But what about the penguins?

51:19.459 --> 51:21.626
And Grandad?

51:22.667 --> 51:24.584
Sometimes you just
have to trust that

51:24.751 --> 51:27.042
maybe I know some things
that you don't.

51:27.209 --> 51:29.417
Maybe I know
some things you don't.

51:29.584 --> 51:31.417
Like...?

51:32.459 --> 51:35.626
Like what? Livvie, what?

51:44.376 --> 51:47.167
Oddball protecting penguins?

51:48.209 --> 51:50.792
Uh...yep.

51:50.959 --> 51:52.917
Is he out there now?

51:56.292 --> 51:57.959
Sorry.

51:58.126 --> 51:59.876
Yep.

52:00.917 --> 52:03.001
Show me.

52:18.251 --> 52:20.751
You realise if anyone
finds out, Oddball's done for?

52:20.917 --> 52:22.876
I mean, you barely escaped
the judge last time.

52:23.042 --> 52:25.042
Yeah, I know.

52:26.084 --> 52:29.167
And that it could all amount
to nothing, anyway.

52:29.334 --> 52:31.667
Uh, yep.

52:31.834 --> 52:34.251
Why now, Dad?

52:35.292 --> 52:37.292
Well, because
they're just little fellas.

52:37.459 --> 52:39.417
They needed a hand.

52:39.584 --> 52:41.334
That's it?

52:41.501 --> 52:43.251
Well, yeah.

52:44.501 --> 52:47.584
Plus...

52:47.751 --> 52:50.042
...when family's
in a bit of strife...

52:51.917 --> 52:54.292
...you got to, you know,

52:54.459 --> 52:57.584
help out, don't ya?

52:59.584 --> 53:02.501
Alright, no rabblerousing
with the government people.

53:02.667 --> 53:05.876
OK, Dad?
Leave the higher-ups to me.

53:06.042 --> 53:09.334
But first, we're gonna need
Bradley's help.

53:09.501 --> 53:11.959
Bradley? No, we can do this
without the circus clown.

53:12.126 --> 53:14.084
I mean, I wouldn't trust
that man with...

53:14.251 --> 53:15.917
- Dad, listen to me.
- Grandad!

53:16.084 --> 53:18.001
- What?
-She's in.

53:18.167 --> 53:20.167
She's what? She's in?

53:20.334 --> 53:22.084
She is?

53:23.126 --> 53:26.251
Oh, good. No, no. Great!

53:27.709 --> 53:29.084
- Dad?
-What?

53:29.251 --> 53:32.001
- My way.
-Yes, love.

53:32.167 --> 53:34.334
Of course. Your way.

53:34.501 --> 53:37.292
Yeah. Uh-huh.

53:37.459 --> 53:39.876
Oddball
on the island?

53:40.042 --> 53:41.959
I can't believe
this is happening.

53:42.126 --> 53:44.126
I know. It's...

53:44.292 --> 53:47.501
I mean, it...it's incredible.
lt really works.

53:47.667 --> 53:50.501
And...and penguin numbers
are finally holding steady,

53:50.667 --> 53:52.626
and right before
breeding season.

53:52.792 --> 53:54.709
We just need Oddball to keep
doing what he's doing and...

53:54.876 --> 53:56.959
- Wow.
-So I thought that perhaps,

53:57.126 --> 53:59.042
if a certain tourism expert

53:59.209 --> 54:02.667
could help us
sway the judge, then...

54:02.834 --> 54:06.001
- Emily. Hi.
-Oh. Jack.

54:06.167 --> 54:08.209
- Jack?
-Jack!

54:08.376 --> 54:10.501
Sorry, I couldn't find anyone
to trade shifts with me,

54:10.667 --> 54:12.584
but I'm gonna be back
out on the island

54:12.751 --> 54:14.667
-as soon as I'm off here.
-OK. Um...

54:14.834 --> 54:17.584
Wow, you look really different.

54:17.751 --> 54:21.501
Jack. Hey! Bradley Slater.

54:21.667 --> 54:23.959
Can you get us
a bottle of shiraz, please?

54:24.126 --> 54:27.251
Yeah, alright. Yep.

54:28.584 --> 54:31.417
Um, wow.
That was a bit rude.

54:31.584 --> 54:33.834
I'm sorry. I have something
I need to tell you.

54:34.001 --> 54:36.251
- OK.
-Um...

54:36.417 --> 54:39.167
I know how much
the penguins mean to you.

54:39.334 --> 54:42.334
Um, but...

54:42.501 --> 54:45.417
...the council are backing
Rich's whale watching centre

54:45.584 --> 54:47.501
on Middle Island.

54:47.667 --> 54:49.709
Once everybody realised

54:49.876 --> 54:52.751
that the island was
becoming uninhabited...

54:52.917 --> 54:54.917
Uh, What?

54:55.084 --> 54:57.751
You didn't think to tell me
anything during all of this?

54:57.917 --> 55:00.626
I wanted to wait
until it was final.

55:00.792 --> 55:04.126
- Final?
-Final?

55:04.292 --> 55:06.209
Right, I've heard
enough of this rubbish.

55:06.376 --> 55:09.501
- Grandad, no!
-I knew we couldn't trust him.

55:09.667 --> 55:12.709
Stop! You can't just
barge in like this. Stop!

55:12.876 --> 55:15.084
The sanctuary's been going
downhill for a while.

55:15.251 --> 55:17.334
At least this will give it
something to replace it

55:17.501 --> 55:20.584
that's honourable, and we can
think about our future.

55:20.751 --> 55:24.376
Stop right there!
What is this I hear

55:24.542 --> 55:26.709
about some whale watching
thing on Middle Island?!

55:26.876 --> 55:28.792
- Dad...
-Mr Marsh...

55:28.959 --> 55:30.876
Listen, you clown,
Middle Island is home

55:31.042 --> 55:33.001
to those penguins
and it's where they belong.

55:33.167 --> 55:35.084
--Oh! Ow!

55:35.251 --> 55:37.042
What was that?

55:37.209 --> 55:41.209
- Ugh! What is this?
-lt's a two-way.

55:41.376 --> 55:43.959
He doesn't care about
the penguins, he's just trying

55:44.126 --> 55:46.251
to feather his own nest, and
he wants you and Livvie in it.

55:46.417 --> 55:48.584
Right, that's enough,
from both of you.

55:48.751 --> 55:51.084
We'll catch a taxi.
Come on. Come on.

55:51.251 --> 55:52.626
<i>Ahh...</i>

55:52.792 --> 55:55.001
You know, if you had one ounce
of feelings for her...

55:55.167 --> 55:57.001
I care about Emily very much,
thank you.

55:57.167 --> 55:59.417
Then help us prove that
Oddball's fair dinkum.

56:00.459 --> 56:03.001
-And if his dinkum...

56:03.167 --> 56:05.459
...proves fair?

56:10.042 --> 56:11.792
Jack.

56:11.959 --> 56:13.876
...then the whale watching
centre will go away

56:14.042 --> 56:16.084
and I'll be out of a job.

56:19.501 --> 56:22.751
- Could you sit down, please?
-Sorry.

56:58.709 --> 57:02.834
This Oddball solution of yours

57:03.001 --> 57:05.251
really works?

57:05.417 --> 57:08.001
Like scrambled eggs on toast.

57:11.626 --> 57:14.292
So, Emily came
to see me about Oddball.

57:15.334 --> 57:17.667
People are looking to council
for something special

57:17.834 --> 57:20.584
to bring in jobs and money,
hence the whales.

57:20.751 --> 57:23.251
This might be my undoing
as a mayor,

57:23.417 --> 57:27.834
but the penguins
have always felt special to me.

57:28.001 --> 57:30.167
The one thing Judge Burns

57:30.334 --> 57:32.834
loves more than his bike
is the law.

57:33.001 --> 57:36.542
When I point out how exposed
the entire whale development is

57:36.709 --> 57:38.626
on account of being approved

57:38.792 --> 57:40.959
before the sanctuary
was legally available,

57:41.126 --> 57:43.126
he'll walk Oddball
on that island himself

57:43.292 --> 57:45.376
in his rush for due diligence.

57:45.542 --> 57:48.459
- Huh.

57:50.959 --> 57:53.167
You're a clever egg,
aren't you?

57:53.334 --> 57:55.709
I didn't become mayor
for nothing.

57:55.876 --> 57:58.251
We'll keep that dog
on the island.

57:58.417 --> 58:00.709
But be warned,
when they're forced

58:00.876 --> 58:02.792
to put their plans on hold,

58:02.959 --> 58:05.876
our approval ratings might
be in for a bit of a hammering.

58:06.042 --> 58:10.876
Oh, that's my
strategic advantage.

58:11.042 --> 58:13.584
- No-one approves of me, anyway.

58:15.834 --> 58:17.709
I don't mind you.

58:35.542 --> 58:37.959
This is a major setback.

58:38.126 --> 58:41.667
- This...this is major.
-Don't put this on me.

58:41.834 --> 58:43.751
You were the one
that convinced me

58:43.917 --> 58:46.001
to keep that dog around
in the first place.

58:48.126 --> 58:50.417
My office,
they think I'm a flip-flopper,

58:50.584 --> 58:52.501
'cause it's penguins
and then it's whales

58:52.667 --> 58:54.751
and then it's whales
and then it's penguins.

58:56.292 --> 58:58.667
Between you and me,

58:58.834 --> 59:02.792
I haven't had a project work
in years.

59:02.959 --> 59:06.709
So I could really use this.

59:06.876 --> 59:09.834
That's not really my problem.

59:10.001 --> 59:12.334
Now, scoot.

59:12.501 --> 59:14.584
OK.

59:16.042 --> 59:18.126
I hate that dog.

59:42.792 --> 59:45.334
-

01:00:19.542 --> 01:00:21.376
Oddball?

01:00:25.709 --> 01:00:27.334
Livvie.

01:00:29.626 --> 01:00:31.167
Livvie.

01:00:32.376 --> 01:00:36.334
Six killed. We're under ten.
And we can't find Oddball.

01:00:39.584 --> 01:00:43.292
We'll, er...we'll find Oddy.

01:00:43.459 --> 01:00:46.042
Get this sorted out.

01:00:46.209 --> 01:00:48.167
We can still fix this,
sweetheart.

01:00:48.334 --> 01:00:52.167
It doesn't matter anymore.
We're moving to New York.

01:00:58.167 --> 01:01:01.251
Sweetheart,
go help Jack and Zoe, OK?

01:01:03.917 --> 01:01:05.667
So, you're moving?

01:01:05.834 --> 01:01:07.751
What am I sticking
around here for?

01:01:07.917 --> 01:01:09.834
Because this works.

01:01:10.001 --> 01:01:12.501
Come on. Oddball wouldn't
have just run off somewhere.

01:01:12.667 --> 01:01:15.167
Stop! I hope Oddball's OK.

01:01:15.334 --> 01:01:17.584
But as far as I go,
the sanctuary's done.

01:01:18.626 --> 01:01:22.501
What, so that's it?
Just give up?

01:01:22.667 --> 01:01:24.792
How dare you!

01:01:24.959 --> 01:01:28.459
Do you even realise what plans
I gave up when Mum died?

01:01:29.501 --> 01:01:31.459
Well, yes.

01:01:31.626 --> 01:01:34.251
But l...l didn't ask you
to do that.

01:01:34.417 --> 01:01:37.001
No, you retreated
to your chickens

01:01:37.167 --> 01:01:40.417
and left her life's work
blowing in the wind.

01:01:42.459 --> 01:01:44.042
Em.

01:01:45.126 --> 01:01:47.834
I didn't just lose a wife.

01:01:48.001 --> 01:01:49.917
I lost my best friend.

01:01:50.084 --> 01:01:53.584
Oh, yes. But I lost my mum.

01:01:56.209 --> 01:01:58.126
<i>L...</i>

01:01:58.292 --> 01:02:01.626
But I knew that the right thing
to do was to continue her work.

01:02:03.334 --> 01:02:06.001
It was my decision, yes,
no regrets,

01:02:06.167 --> 01:02:09.167
but it is 11 years later and...

01:02:09.334 --> 01:02:11.251
"Dad, the penguins are gone.

01:02:11.417 --> 01:02:13.501
You know, I used to have fun.

01:02:13.667 --> 01:02:15.667
I used to be a lot of fun.

01:02:15.834 --> 01:02:18.917
I didn't get to go to
university or see the world,

01:02:19.084 --> 01:02:21.751
but I'm gonna make damn sure
that Olivia does.

01:02:55.417 --> 01:02:57.459
Oddball!

01:03:00.501 --> 01:03:02.376
Oddball!

01:03:15.792 --> 01:03:18.126
Oddball!

01:03:18.292 --> 01:03:20.042
Where are you, mate?

01:03:21.084 --> 01:03:23.876
Oddball!

01:03:25.334 --> 01:03:27.959
Oddball!

01:03:32.584 --> 01:03:34.792
Oddball!

01:04:33.126 --> 01:04:34.751
Hi, love.

01:04:39.459 --> 01:04:41.917
It's been a, er...
it's been a while

01:04:42.084 --> 01:04:44.376
since you've heard from me.

01:04:49.959 --> 01:04:52.209
Just want you to know
